# pysisense — Project Overview

`pysisense` is an official Python SDK for the **Sisense BI platform**. It wraps the Sisense REST API into a structured, class-based library for automation, migrations, and health checks.

## Modules

| Module | Class | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| `sisenseclient.py` | `SisenseClient` | Base HTTP client, auth, logging, shared session |
| `access_management.py` | `AccessManagement` | Users, groups, permissions, ownership, RLS, schedules |
| `dashboard.py` | `Dashboard` | Dashboard CRUD, share management, script injection |
| `datamodel.py` | `DataModel` | Schema provisioning, builds, connections, datasecurity |
| `migration.py` | `Migration` | Cross-environment migrations (users, groups, dashboards, models) |
| `wellcheck.py` | `WellCheck` | Health/complexity checks across dashboards and data models |
| `utils.py` | — | `convert_to_dataframe`, `export_to_csv`, `convert_utc_to_local` |

## Config

Authentication is configured via a YAML file:
```yaml
domain: your-sisense-instance.com
token: your-api-token
is_ssl: true
```

Or inline: `SisenseClient(domain=..., token=..., is_ssl=True)`

## Examples and docs

- `examples/*.md` — copy-paste workflow guides; **not meant to be executed end-to-end**. Copy relevant snippets into your own scripts, update YAML paths and IDs, then run.
- `docs/*.md` — full module-level reference documentation.

## Tooling

- Package manager: `uv`
- Lint + format: `ruff` (line length 200)
- Commits: `commitizen` (conventional commits)
- Versioning: `python-semantic-release`
- Pre-commit hooks: ruff + commitizen
